originalText.text: Diaby is super caring and detailed. She always aims to give you just what you want. Even if she has to take extra time. You’ll always leave happy and content. Yes it takes hours as she is highly requested, don’t shy away it’ll be worth your time.

originalText.text:
If you want your hair to simply be presentable, do yourself a favor & STAY AWAY from this place. I would pay a million dollars not to feel this hideous. Terrible experience & above it all, worse hairstyle I’ve ever had in my 30 years of existence. The braids are brolic & she pulled out half of my hair thought the process. Now I have to wear a hat for the next 2 weeks & yet I was told to pay more than the average price for this hairstyle . I don’t understand how one can even own a salon or call themselves  a hair dresser knowing there’s absolutely no consideration for their customers satisfaction or just how crazy they’ll looking waking in the streets with such atrocious hair. I blame myself for not leaving after seeing what he customer before myself hair looked like. I don’t normally leave reviews, but this experience has honestly left a scar & I don’t see myself ever again going to an African hair braiding salon to do any style. I’m so upset & sad that my money has gone to waste & my hair is too tight to even consider redoing it. The moment she started braiding my baby hair with extensions, I should’ve known to run out of that salon. I wouldn’t recommend this place to an enemy. I would’ve just walked away & dealt with my hair just being a bad experience, but I’m so baffled by how much the hair dresser just wanted to get paid. So congratulations to you, y out got paid & unfortunately for me, I walked away looking worse than how I came.

Upset is an understatement, I feel bullied & used.

originalText.text: I let a text message with a picture of the style I wanted. The owner didn't get back to me til' close to 10pm. I texted her the following day about setting up and appt. She never returned my text. I ended up going to the spot to find them closed with lights on. I called and she wouldn't be coming in til' 4pm. I ended up going to another spot.
